I need to identify the specific line item and value related to the increase in tax accrued but not yet paid.

Looking at the cash flow statement provided, I can see that there is a line item called "Increase (Decrease) in Tax Payable" with a value of 131850.51. This is exactly what we're looking for since:

1. "Tax Payable" represents taxes that have been accrued but not yet paid
2. The positive value (131850.51) indicates there was an increase in this amount
3. This line item appears in the Cash Flow From Operating Activities section, which is the standard location for changes in tax payable

Therefore, the value representing the increase in tax accrued but not yet paid is 131850.51.
